

 1пёҸвғЈ What is an IAM Policy?

IAM Policy ek JSON document hota hai jo define karta hai:

вҶ’ Who (user / group / role)
вҶ’ Can do what (actions like `s3:GetObject`)
вҶ’ On which resource (S3 bucket, EC2, etc.)
вҶ’ Under what condition

рҹ‘ү Simple words me:
Policy = Rule book of permissions

---

 2пёҸвғЈ Types of Policies in AWS

AWS me mainly 2 broad categories hoti hain:

 вһӨ IAM Policies

 вһӨ Resource Policies

---

 3пёҸвғЈ IAM Policies (Most Common)

IAM Policies directly IAM identities par lagti hain:

вҶ’ User
вҶ’ Group
вҶ’ Role

IAM Policies ke 2 types hote hain рҹ‘Ү

---

 4пёҸвғЈ Inline Policies

 рҹ”№ What is Inline Policy?

вҶ’ Policy jo directly ek IAM entity (user / role / group) ke andar embedded hoti hai
вҶ’ One-to-One relationship maintain karti hai
вҶ’ Reusable вқҢ
вҶ’ Versioning вқҢ

 рҹ”№ Important Point

Agar IAM user delete ho gaya вҶ’
рҹ‘ү Inline policy automatically delete ho jaati hai

 рҹ”№ Real-World Example

Suppose:
вҶ’ Ek temporary employee hai
вҶ’ Sirf ek hi EC2 instance ka access dena hai
вҶ’ Future me reuse nahi karna

рҹ‘ү Best choice: Inline Policy

 рҹ”№ When to Use Inline Policy?

вҶ’ Very specific permission
вҶ’ Short-term requirement
вҶ’ Tight control needed

---

 5пёҸвғЈ Managed Policies

 рҹ”№ What is Managed Policy?

вҶ’ Standalone policy hoti hai
вҶ’ Multiple users, groups, roles par attach ho sakti hai
вҶ’ Reusable вң…
вҶ’ Versioning supported вң…

рҹ‘ү Ye production environment me most recommended hoti hai

---

 6пёҸвғЈ Types of Managed Policies

 1пёҸвғЈ AWS Managed Policies

вҶ’ AWS khud create aur manage karta hai
вҶ’ Common use cases ke liye ready-made

Examples:
вҶ’ `AmazonS3FullAccess`
вҶ’ `AmazonEC2ReadOnlyAccess`
вҶ’ `AdministratorAccess`

рҹ“Ң Best for beginners & standard roles

---

 2пёҸвғЈ Customer Managed Policies

вҶ’ Customer khud create karta hai
вҶ’ Specific business requirement ke according

 рҹ”№ Real-World Example

Company roles:
вҶ’ Developer вҶ’ EC2 + S3 limited access
вҶ’ QA вҶ’ Read-only access
вҶ’ Admin вҶ’ Full access

рҹ‘ү Ek policy bana ke multiple users/groups ko attach kar sakte ho

---

 7пёҸвғЈ Resource Policies

 рҹ”№ What is Resource Policy?

вҶ’ Policy resource ke upar attach hoti hai
вҶ’ Identity ke upar nahi

Examples of resources:
вҶ’ S3 Bucket
вҶ’ VPC Endpoint
вҶ’ KMS Key
вҶ’ API Gateway
вҶ’ Lambda Function

 рҹ”№ Real-World Example

вҶ’ S3 bucket ko allow karna:

 Account A
 Account B

рҹ‘ү Ye kaam Resource Policy se hota hai (Bucket Policy)

рҹ“Ң Cross-account access ke liye Resource Policy mandatory hoti hai

